   Review of warrior disciplines</span><hr size=1> Evasive: extreme disappointment, very minimal effects.<br>
<br>
Charge: It's useful on mobs with very high ac, otherwise just a stepping stone until you get mightystrike.<br>
<br>
Mightystrike: Thumbs up, the true power of this is however can only be obtained by getting all the shaman/cleric hp/ac buffs, then waiting until you are berserk to use it, you will do very nice damage via crippling blows, the reuse time is fairly high however.<br>
<br>
Defensive: Excellent in groups where I'm the only tank, significant reduction in damage taken.<br>
<br>
Furious: I'm not 56 yet, but looks excellent in groups where i'm the only tank, but whenever casters mention this and the 54 discipline to me they always mention getting a weighted axe and tearing up, kind of tired of hearing that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Precision: Doesn't look great on paper.<br>
<br>
Fell Strike: From all reports this will be THE general purpose discipline, outdamaging mightystrike, and Defensive/Furious have limited use in groups with multiple melee classes, really looking forward to this.<br>
<br>
Fortitude: Warrior Divine Aura, this has it's uses and I can see this especially being useful in sebilis.<br>
<br>
Aggressive: Furor from FoH has said it is broken and useless. <p>Nillon, level 55 Myrmidon, Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uffawsupbludboilur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ffawsup Bludboilur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/18/00 4:53:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Review of warrior disciplines</span><hr size=1> Evasive: extreme disappointment, very minimal effects.<br>
<br>
*** Agreed.  I notice little/no difference in getting hit using this discipline.<br>
<br>
Charge: It's useful on mobs with very high ac, otherwise just a stepping stone until you get mightystrike.<br>
<br>
*** My personal favorite.  Using dual wield and hasted, I can deal out a TON of damage with this.  Using this discipline at the right time can mean the difference between winning a tough battle or having a dead party.<br>
<br>
Mightystrike: Thumbs up, the true power of this is however can only be obtained by getting all the shaman/cleric hp/ac buffs, then waiting until you are berserk to use it, you will do very nice damage via crippling blows, the reuse time is fairly high however.<br>
<br>
*** I've seen Grrumble use this with fantastic effect.  It's a great discipline if used as Nillon describes, especially with a high damage 2H weapon.<br>
<br>
Defensive: Excellent in groups where I'm the only tank, significant reduction in damage taken.<br>
<br>
*** While it does cut down on damage, I haven't noticed it preventing that much.  I probably haven't used it enough to determine its value yet, but currently would rank it only a step above Evasive.<br>
<br>
Furious: I'm not 56 yet, but looks excellent in groups where i'm the only tank, but whenever casters mention this and the 54 discipline to me they always mention getting a weighted axe and tearing up, kind of tired of hearing that  <br>
<br>
*** This one is great if you are the last hope of your party evac'ing or making it to the zone.  I used this in The Hole this weekend when we were overrun by Golems.  I tagged all the MOBs, got them on me, dragged them to the far corner of the room and when I got down to one bubble, fired off Furious and riposted for the 9 seconds.  Just enough time to allow some of the players there to either gate or camp as needed.  This one can be a god-send in certain situations.<br>
<br>
Precision: Doesn't look great on paper.<br>
<br>
*** I'll let you know this week - only a bubble to 57.<br>
<br>
Fell Strike: From all reports this will be THE general purpose discipline, outdamaging mightystrike, and Defensive/Furious have limited use in groups with multiple melee classes, really looking forward to this.<br>
<br>
*** This does look good.<br>
<br>
Fortitude: Warrior Divine Aura, this has it's uses and I can see this especially being useful in sebilis.<br>
<br>
*** Haven't really looked at this one yet as 59 is sooooo far away...<br>
<br>
Aggressive: Furor from FoH has said it is broken and useless. <br>
<br>
*** =(<br>
<br>
Overall, a couple of the disciplines are very nice, some are average, and a few I will hardly ever use.  I personally think the effective times should be increased a bit (9 seconds isn't a whole lot), but the recovery times seem to be about right.  Verant did a pretty good job on these, and I hope they spend a bit of time fine-tuning them.<br>
<br>
-- Ffawsup Bludboilur<br>
